{
  "texts": [
    "(Distinguishability condition).",
    "We say n-qubit quantum states ρ 1, …, ρ N fulfill the distinguishability condition if we can find intermediate states ρ i 7!ρ i based on some generic quantum state approximation protocol such that they fulfill the following:1.",
    "For each i ∈ [N], ρi is efficiently preparable with a PQC.2.",
    "The matrix Ŵ can be efficiently constructed, with entriesŴ i,j = trðρ i ρj Þ:ð16Þ3.",
    "The matrix Ŵ is well-conditioned.Notable examples of approximation protocols are those inspired by classical shadows 77 or tensor networks 78."
  ]
}